🧩 User Story

Title
User identification via RFID badge with IMEX fallback and mandatory confirmation

As a
Visitor / employee using a comptoir

I want
To be automatically identified by scanning my RFID badge

So that
My check-in is faster while ensuring my identity is accurate

⸻

🎯 Description

When a user scans their RFID badge on the tablet:

* The application first attempts identification using the local badge collection
* If the badge is unknown or rejected, it queries the IMEX API
* In all cases (local or IMEX), user confirmation is mandatory
* If no match is found, the user must manually enter their UID
* Every association is stored locally with a source (Manual or IMEX)

⸻

✅ Acceptance Criteria

🔹 Case 1 — Badge found locally and confirmed

Given the Tag ID exists in the local collection
When the user scans their badge
Then the associated UID is displayed
And the user is asked to confirm their identity
And if confirmed, the journey continues

⸻

🔹 Case 2 — Badge found locally but rejected

Given the Tag ID exists in the local collection
When the user rejects the proposed identity
Then the local association is deleted
And the application queries the IMEX API

⸻

🔹 Case 3 — Badge not found locally but found in IMEX

Given the Tag ID does not exist locally
When the application queries IMEX
And IMEX returns a UID
Then the UID is displayed
And the user must confirm their identity
And if confirmed:

* the association is stored locally
* with source = IMEX
* the journey continues

⸻

🔹 Case 4 — IMEX result rejected

Given IMEX returns a UID
When the user rejects the identity
Then the association is not kept
And the user must manually enter their UID

⸻

🔹 Case 5 — Badge not found in IMEX

Given IMEX returns no result
When the user scans their badge
Then a message indicates the card is not recognized
And the user must manually enter their UID

⸻

🔹 Case 6 — Manual entry

Given the user manually enters their UID
Then the Tag ID / UID association is stored locally
And with source = Manual
And the journey continues

⸻

⚙️ Business Rules

* User confirmation is mandatory in all cases (local or IMEX)
* A “No” response always deletes the local association
* The IMEX API is used only:
    * when the badge is not found locally
    * or after a user rejection
* The local collection acts as a cache and resilience layer

⸻

📦 Data Model (simplified)

Badge
- tagId (string)
- uid (string)
- source (IMEX | Manual)
- createdAt
- updatedAt

⸻

🚨 Edge Cases

* IMEX API unavailable:
    * fallback directly to manual UID entry
* Invalid UID entered:
    * error message and retry
* Shared or incorrectly assigned badge:
    * corrected via user rejection mechanism

⸻

💡 Future Enhancements (optional)

* Add a confidence level on associations
* Track rejection history to detect IMEX inconsistencies
* Pre-fill UID based on context (SSO, session, etc.)

